                <head>No. 59.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. Fish to General Schenck</hi>. (<hi rend="italic"
                        >Communicated by Mr. Moran, May</hi> 25, 11.45 <hi rend="italic"
                    >a.m.</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1872-05-25">May 25, 1872</date>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegraphic.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">[From British Blue Book “North America,” No. 9, (1372,) p. 23.]</p>
                <p>The Senate will undoubtedly amend the proposed Article. The terms of the note to
                    the Arbitrators cannot be fixed until the language of the Article is agreed
                    upon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
